ideology_summary: Cluster 0 exhibits a moderately liberal ideology overall, with negative means on abortion (-0.18), redistribution (-0.27), health (-0.09), trans laws (-0.56), minority representation (-0.36), and DEI/affirmative action (-0.83), while showing conservative leanings on defense (+1.72), environment (+0.57), Israel aid (+0.32), and Ukraine aid (+0.40). Variation is highest in defense (SD=1.50) and vaccines (SD=1.06), indicating heterogeneity in these domains, whereas racial disparity (SD=0.30) and democracy (SD=0.42) show more consensus. The cluster has moderate ideological homogeneity (avg z-dist=5.326) and features moderate economic vulnerability (mean=3.94), with a partisan composition leaning toward Harris supporters (39.2%) and a substantial non-voting segment (28.5%).

Cluster 1 exhibits a moderately conservative ideology overall, with positive means on abortion (+0.10), immigration (+0.25), redistribution (+0.25), efficacy/trust/corruption (+0.31), vaccines (+0.35), Israel aid (+0.28), and party ID leaning strongly toward Trump (61.8%). Domains like health (-0.26), defense (-0.27), democracy (-0.28), trans laws (-0.20), and minority representation (-0.50) show more liberal stances. Variation is moderate to high in domains such as trans laws (SD=1.02) and gay rights (SD=0.93), indicating heterogeneity, while racial disparity (SD=0.21) and democracy (SD=0.23) are more homogeneous. Economic vulnerability is moderate (mean 2.89), suggesting some economic concerns within this group.
